spanishExample: ¡Trata de ir ocho veces! Nosotros también tratamos de hacer lo mismo.
englishTranslation: Try to go eight times! We also are trying to do the same.
vocabIncluded: "lo": "the" with no noun, as in "lo bueno"
de used after Tratar to mean “try to”
tratamos: try, we try (Tratar, present, 1st person plural)

spanishExample: Acabas de hablar con los chicos de dieciséis y diecinueve años.
englishTranslation: You just talked to the sixteen- and nineteen-year-old boys.
vocabIncluded: acabas: finish, you finish (Acabar, present, 2nd person)
hablar: to speak / to talk (Hablar infinitive)

spanishExample: Acabó las veinte películas, pero solo tenía que ver quince.
englishTranslation: He finished the twenty movies, but he only had to watch fifteen.
vocabIncluded: acabó: finished, he/she/it finished (Acabar, preterite, 3rd person)
using Tener with "que" to indicate obligation

spanishExample: Ayer vinieron once personas, pero hoy vinieron veintisiete.
englishTranslation: Yesterday eleven people came, but today twenty-seven came.

spanishExample: Cuando era niño, trataba de tener catorce.
englishTranslation: When I was a kid(m), I used to try to have fourteen.
vocabIncluded: de used after Tratar to mean “try to”
trataba: tried, I tried (Tratar, imperfect, 1st person)

spanishExample: Él trata de ver esos veinticuatro edificios.
englishTranslation: He's trying to see those twenty-four buildings.
vocabIncluded: de used after Tratar to mean “try to”
trata: tries, he/she/it tries (Tratar, present, 3rd person)

spanishExample: En esa habitación vi solo veintiuno, pero trataré de ver más.
englishTranslation: In that bedroom I saw only twenty-one, but I’ll try to see more.
vocabIncluded: de used after Tratar to mean “try to”
trataré: will try , I will try (Tratar, future, 1st person)
vi: saw, I saw (Ver, preterite, 1st person)

spanishExample: Eso se acabará pronto.
englishTranslation: That will run out soon.
vocabIncluded: acabarse: any use of acabar with a reflexive pronoun, changing the meaning to run out)
acabará: will finish, he/she/it will finish (Acabar, future, 3rd person)

spanishExample: Esos veintiún hombres tienen entre dieciocho y veintitrés años.
englishTranslation: Those twenty-one men are between eighteen and twenty-three years old.
vocabIncluded: tener X años: to be X years old (idiom)

spanishExample: Estamos tratando de hablar con diez personas, no con veintiocho.
englishTranslation: We’re trying to talk with ten people, not with twenty-eight.
vocabIncluded: de used after Tratar to mean “try to”
hablar: to speak / to talk (Hablar infinitive)

spanishExample: Había solo cinco o siete personas, pero se suponía que iban a venir doce.
englishTranslation: There were only five or seven people, but supposedly twelve were going to come.
vocabIncluded: "o": "or" when used between items in a list
"que", meaning "that" as a conjunction (even in cases where "that" disappears in English)
había: "there was/were" indicating existence (Haber, imperfect, impersonal)
iban: "were going", "they were going" (Ir, imperfect, 3rd person plural)
supone: supposes, he/she/it supposes (Suponer, present, 3rd person)
suponerse: any use of Suponer with a reflexive, plus "que", pronoun, changing the meaning to "supposedly"
using Ir and "a" to put verbs in the future (e.g. "voy a ser")

spanishExample: Hay tres o cuatro baños en esa casa.
englishTranslation: There are three or four bathrooms in that house.
vocabIncluded: "o": "or" when used between items in a list
hay: "there is/are" indicating existence (Haber, present, impersonal)

spanishExample: Hay veintiséis mujeres en la fiesta, no veintiuna.
englishTranslation: There are twenty-six women at the party, not twenty-one.
vocabIncluded: hay: "there is/are" indicating existence (Haber, present, impersonal)

spanishExample: He tratado de hablar con el tipo de veintidós años.
englishTranslation: I’ve tried talking to the twenty-two-year-old dude.
vocabIncluded: de used after Tratar to mean “try to”
hablar: to speak / to talk (Hablar infinitive)
he: "have", "I have" before a participle (Haber, present, 1st person)

spanishExample: La historia se trata de nueve personas que tienen veinticinco años.
englishTranslation: The story is about nine people who are twenty-five years old.
vocabIncluded: tener X años: to be X years old (idiom)
trata: tries, he/she/it tries (Tratar, present, 3rd person)

spanishExample: Mis padres solo me daban trece.
englishTranslation: My parents only used to give me thirteen.
vocabIncluded: me: "me" as an indirect object ("to me", "for me")

spanishExample: Solo ha visto veintiuno.
englishTranslation: He has only seen twenty-one.
vocabIncluded: ha: "has", "he/she/it has" before a participle (Haber, present, 3rd person)

spanishExample: Los niños de esta clase tienen ocho, once y trece años.
englishTranslation: The kids in this class are eight, eleven, and thirteen years old.
vocabIncluded: tener X años: to be X years old (idiom)

hablar: to speak / to talk (Hablar infinitive)

englishTranslation: We tried to have twenty-nine.
vocabIncluded: de used after Tratar to mean “try to”
tratamos: tried, we tried (Tratar, preterite, 1st person plural)

spanishExample: Tratan de tener diecisiete de esos.
englishTranslation: They’re trying to have seventeen of those.

tratan: try, they try (Tratar, present, 3rd person plural)
